  "rationale": "Supervisor is organized into: (1) safe navigation (clear), (2) obstacle-specific recovery (obs_front/left/right -> back/rotate -> scan), and (3) marker acquisition/approach (scan/search -> marker_track -> marker_approach). Marker_close is handled globally by transitioning to a terminal goal state where stop is the only controllable. Commit/scan/recovery states are one-shot on their primary controllable and then return to a decision state. Uncontrollable events are fully covered per state with self-loops in action/commit/scan/recovery states to prevent preemption, while safety-critical obstacle_* and marker_close force leaving those states.",
