  "strategy": [
    "In clear/search, prioritize marker acquisition: if marker_seen occurs, switch to marker_track/marker_approach where move_to_marker is the primary controllable.",
    "If marker_lost during tracking/approach, immediately go to scan_full to reacquire rather than continuing blindly.",
    "Safety-first obstacle handling: obstacle_front/left/right force transitions to dedicated recovery states (obs_front/obs_left/obs_right) that lead to scan/rotation rather than move_forward.",
    "Avoid oscillations: obs_left prefers clockwise rotation; obs_right prefers counterclockwise rotation; both route through scan/search after the one-shot rotation.",
    "Commit/scan/recovery states are one-shot: their primary controllable transitions out to a decision/perception state (clear/search_decision/scan_full), preventing infinite controllable loops.",
    "Global goal condition: whenever marker_close occurs in any state, transition to goal_stop where stop is the only effective action."
  ]
